  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study is noted in the UQ narrative to identify potentially influential parameters, but no structured sensitivity analysis record has been linked to this package. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
