    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification with 1500 samples has been completed and 95% prediction intervals on hemolysis index satisfy the acceptance criterion at all five operating points. The UQ narrative references a screening sensitivity study conducted prior to Monte Carlo sampling, which informally identified hemolysis power-law coefficients as likely dominant contributors. On the basis of the factor assessments and UQ coverage, the credibility package is accepted for the stated COU. Note: the structured sensitivity analysis record was not formally linked to this package; the dominant input driver characterization rests on the verbal description in the UQ report rather than a registered sensitivity analysis artifact.",
